Add this task just before the “Append per-JVM result” task:

- name: Safe source_map lookup
  set_fact:
    _src_map: "{{ source_map | default({}) }}"
    _discovery_source: >-
      {{
        (
          (source_map | default({})).get(result_jvm_norm, 'unknown')
          if (source_map | default({})) is mapping
          else 'unknown'
        )
      }}
  changed_when: false

Then in the “Append per-JVM result” task, use _discovery_source:

- name: Append per-JVM result (includes discovery_source)
  set_fact:
    jvm_results: >-
      {{
        jvm_results + [
          {
            'env_name': (env_name | default('na')),
            'env_host_profile_jvm': ((env_name | default('na')) ~ ':' ~ inventory_hostname ~ ':' ~ (profile_dir | basename) ~ ':' ~ result_jvm_norm),
            'status': ( 'success' if started_ok else 'failed' ),
            'profile_dir': profile_dir,
            'cell_name': cell_name,
            'new_pid': new_pid,
            'discovery_source': _discovery_source,
            'action': ( 'restart' if (result_jvm_norm in (jvms_started_pre | default([]))) else 'start' ),
            'reason': ( '' if started_ok else ('Not STARTED after operations (missing: ' ~ _expected_started_line ~ ')') )
          }
        ]
      }}

This guarantees:

if source_map is missing → 'unknown'
if source_map exists but isn’t a dict → 'unknown'
if it’s a dict → .get() works safely
Also make sure source_map is passed into the profile batch include

